    <p class="faq-question"> What does it mean for CO<sub>2</sub>IN in beta testing? </p>
    <p class="faq-answer" id="getting-started"> This means that CO<sub>2</sub>IN is only being released to a limited set of people, that the kinks are still being worked out, and that CO<sub>2</sub>IN account balances may be reset to zero upon completion of the BETA. Use at your own risk.</p>

    <p class="faq-question"> OK, I'm sold - I want to help reduce emissions. Or I want to play around with a new cryptocurrency. How the heck do I get started with this thing? </p>
    <div class="faq-answer">
        <p> Start by downloading the official CO<sub>2</sub>IN client. Builds exist for <%= link_to 'Windows', download_win_url %> and <%= link_to 'OS X', download_osx_url %>. Afterwards, you will need to place the following <%= link_to 'configuration file', download_cnf_url %> in one of the following places: </p>
        <ul>
            <li> Windows: C:\Users\[username]\AppData\Roaming\CO2IN, substituting [username] for your username. </li>
            <li> Mac OS X: /User/[username]/Library/Application Support/CO2IN/, substituting [username] for your username. </li>
        </ul>
        <p> This file will ensure that you connect to valid nodes in the CO<sub>2</sub>IN network and activate mining (see next question) by default. To turn off default mining, just put a "#' character in front of the line that says "gen=1" in the configuration file. </p>
    </div>

    <p class="faq-question"> How do I obtain CO<sub>2</sub>IN? </p>
    <div class="faq-answer"> 
        <p> A computationally-intensive process called mining, which makes CO<sub>2</sub>IN's record of transactions difficult to forge, is rewarded through CO<sub>2</sub>IN. The current reward size is 50 CO2C. To get started with mining simply follow the instructions in the above question. After doing this, you should periodically receive mining rewards when your CO<sub>2</sub>IN is running.</p>
        <p> If you don't want to mine, or are simply eager to get started, simply send an e-mail to the creator with your CO<sub>2</sub>IN address, and he'll send you some (If you're reading this, you probably know who the Creator is). </p>
    </div>
