    <h1 id="implementation" class="page-header">Marketplace</h1>

    <p class="faq-question"> What is the Marketplace? </p>
    <p class="faq-answer"> The Marketplace is an economic experiment targeted at the members of the Aiden Lab based out of the Baylor College of Medicine. Starting on Monday, June 9th, 2014, all snacks provided by the lab will be priced according to the <%= link_to 'Marketplace', marketplace_path %> posted on this website. In order to consume a snack, lab members will need to transfer the listed amount of CO<sub>2</sub>IN to its corresponding deposit address.  </p>

    <p class="faq-question"> That's kind of perverse. What's the point? </p>
    <p class="faq-answer"> We're interesting in collecting on-the-ground data on how money (CO<sub>2</sub>IN) with a clear source of value (snacks) is used by a community of people. Start mining! Or contact the creator with your address to be sent some starter coin. </p>

    <p class="faq-question"> Do prices change? If so, how often? According to what logic? </p>
    <p class="faq-answer"> Yes. We are targeting daily price list changes. The marketplace operators receive 20&#37; of revenues generated on snack sales, so they are incentivized to price snacks in such a way that moves inventory quickly. In short, the prices of in demand snacks should trend higher than those of less popular snacks. </p>

    <p class="faq-question"> Can I use the same deposit address over and over again for given snack? </p>
    <p class="faq-answer"> No. Each time a snack's price changes, the snack's deposit address changes as well. This is for clear accounting of what price (and when) a given snack was purchased. </p>

